Boil a half-full #kettle{}. Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with
@salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for
~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{}
and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, trim the @Courgette{1}, then quarter lengthways. Chop into 1cm
chunks.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

When hot, add the courgette and cook until charred, ~{6-8%minutes} total.
Turn only every couple of mins - this will result in the courgette picking up
some nice colour.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Roughly chop the @Dill{1%bunch} (stalks and all).

Once the courgette is cooked, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then transfer
to a #medium bowl{}. Wipe out the (now empty) frying pan.

Heat the frying pan on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British Beef Mince{240%g}. Fry until the mince has browned,
~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's
> cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}.

Add the garlic, @Chermoula Spice Mix{1%sachet} and @Tomato Puree{30%g} to the
beef. Fry for ~{2%minutes}.

Stir in the @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g} and @Water for the Sauce{100%ml}. Bring
to the boil, then lower to a simmer. Cook until thickened slightly,
~{3-4%minutes}.

In the meantime, in a #small bowl{}, mix together the @Greek Style Natural
Yoghurt{75%g} and dill. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When the beef has finished cooking, stir through the @Honey{15%g}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Stir the charred courgette through the sauce.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water if
you feel it needs it.

Share the rice between your #plates{}.

Top with your chermoula beef and finish with a dollop of dill yoghurt. Enjoy!